WEBVTT

00:03.438 --> 00:03.699
.

00:03.742 --> 00:05.657
- Maybe the three of us,
we could live together

00:05.701 --> 00:06.745
kind of permanently.

00:06.789 --> 00:08.008
- Do you think
my new friend Teddy

00:08.051 --> 00:09.313
can come over to the new place?

00:09.357 --> 00:10.836
- Teddy a teacher from school?
- No.

00:10.880 --> 00:13.752
He's the man who waits
by the fence for me.

00:13.796 --> 00:15.189
- I wanna see the footage.

00:15.232 --> 00:17.756
[tense music]

00:17.800 --> 00:19.193
His name is Theo Morris.

00:19.236 --> 00:20.281
What the hell is going on,
Alana?

00:20.324 --> 00:21.804
- He's Makayla's uncle.

00:21.847 --> 00:23.110
- Oh, Jesus.

00:23.153 --> 00:25.068
- He's filed a petition
for full custody.

00:25.112 --> 00:28.506
[dramatic music]

00:28.550 --> 00:32.380
♪

00:32.423 --> 00:33.903
- Carolina,
we do not understand

00:33.946 --> 00:35.296
how it got this far.

00:35.339 --> 00:36.558
I mean, the only time
this man has spoken

00:36.601 --> 00:38.212
to Makayla is when
he's creeping around

00:38.255 --> 00:39.256
outside of her school.
I mean, this is--

00:39.300 --> 00:40.692
this is insane.

00:40.736 --> 00:42.825
- When Mr. Morris showed
up at Makayla's school,

00:42.868 --> 00:44.348
it wasn't illegal.

00:44.392 --> 00:47.090
He and his wife,
they have a lot of money,

00:47.134 --> 00:49.179
big house, big yard, all that.

00:49.223 --> 00:51.660
And Theo Morris is
a blood relation.

00:51.703 --> 00:53.183
We're talking about
his brother's daughter.

00:53.227 --> 00:54.837
- A brother who's serving life
for murder.

00:54.880 --> 00:55.925
- Adam.
- No.

00:55.968 --> 00:57.100
This is the qualifier?

00:57.144 --> 00:58.406
I mean--
- I understand.

00:58.449 --> 01:00.538
- Tariq Morris killed
Makayla's family.

01:00.582 --> 01:02.845
- I understand,
but in the eyes of the system

01:02.888 --> 01:05.065
there's only one client here.
It's not you.

01:05.108 --> 01:06.631
- Yeah, I know.

01:06.675 --> 01:08.546
- The judge's decision
will rest

01:08.590 --> 01:10.548
only on what's best
for Makayla,

01:10.592 --> 01:13.812
where she's safe,
the stability of the home,

01:13.856 --> 01:16.250
the mental and physical health
of the caretakers.

01:16.293 --> 01:20.123
And being a blood relative
carries a lot of weight.

01:20.167 --> 01:21.298
The truth?

01:21.342 --> 01:23.605
[soft somber music]

01:23.648 --> 01:24.954
You could lose.

01:24.997 --> 01:27.478
You could lose Makayla.

01:27.522 --> 01:30.960
To avoid that,
you need to keep it together.

01:31.003 --> 01:33.093
Do what I say.
We fight,

01:33.136 --> 01:37.053
but we do it calmly,
methodically.

01:37.097 --> 01:40.143
Okay?

01:40.187 --> 01:47.324
♪

01:53.156 --> 01:54.940
- We got this.

01:54.984 --> 01:56.377
We do.

01:58.292 --> 01:59.945
Got some time
before Theo's testimony.

01:59.989 --> 02:02.296
You wanna grab a bit to eat,
think about anything else

02:02.339 --> 02:04.124
for a little while?

02:04.167 --> 02:05.386
- I've got some errands to run,

02:05.429 --> 02:06.952
but why don't we just meet back
here after?

02:06.996 --> 02:08.171
- All right.

02:08.215 --> 02:09.868
You sure
you don't want company?

02:09.912 --> 02:11.174
- I'm good, thanks.

02:11.218 --> 02:14.134
- All right.

02:32.108 --> 02:33.544
- Gang going at it.

02:33.588 --> 02:36.286
Caller reports snow shovel
stolen from his shed,

02:36.330 --> 02:37.331
58th and 10th.

02:37.374 --> 02:38.810
Units in the 9th,

02:38.854 --> 02:40.856
manager of the drugstore
at Pulaski and Bruce

02:40.899 --> 02:42.249
says a couple walked out

02:42.292 --> 02:43.641
with a bag
of stolen toiletries.

02:43.685 --> 02:45.077
They need a report taken.

02:45.121 --> 02:47.515
- Come on.

02:47.558 --> 02:49.517
- Units in the 24th
and citywide,

02:49.560 --> 02:51.171
call of a home invasion,
possible homicide.

02:51.214 --> 02:52.694
3021 Longwood.

02:52.737 --> 02:55.131
- 5021 Eddie,
hold me down responding.

02:55.175 --> 02:58.134
[dramatic music]

02:58.178 --> 03:02.138
♪

03:02.182 --> 03:04.401
Police!
You guys hurt?

03:04.445 --> 03:06.708
- Mr. Page, está muerto.

03:06.751 --> 03:08.536
- Upstairs?

03:08.579 --> 03:10.668
Anyone else in the house?

03:10.712 --> 03:12.279
¿Hay alguien más en la casa?

03:12.322 --> 03:13.715
- No lo sé.

03:13.758 --> 03:14.759
- Okay.

03:14.803 --> 03:15.978
[speaking Spanish]

03:16.021 --> 03:17.675
Go, go, go, go, go!

03:17.719 --> 03:20.156
5021 Eddie, I got two witnesses
sequestered behind my vehicle

03:20.200 --> 03:21.331
for their safety.

03:21.375 --> 03:22.289
Keep the cars rolling,
I'm going in,

03:22.332 --> 03:24.073
and I'm going dark.

03:24.116 --> 03:27.076
[tense music]

03:27.119 --> 03:33.561
♪

03:35.302 --> 03:36.303
[soft thump]

03:36.346 --> 03:43.484
♪

04:06.594 --> 04:09.771
- All right,
go ahead and bag it.

04:09.814 --> 04:12.077
Scrub the house, print
the place floor to ceiling.

04:12.121 --> 04:14.254
- Yes, sir.

04:14.297 --> 04:16.125
- Body was cold,
no blood splatter,

04:16.168 --> 04:18.910
no signs of a struggle,
no defensive wounds.

04:18.954 --> 04:22.262
I think they cut off his hand
after he was dead.

04:23.828 --> 04:25.743
But look at this.

04:25.787 --> 04:28.616
Look, there's...

04:28.659 --> 04:31.445
little bits of flesh
mixed in with the blood.

04:31.488 --> 04:33.795
I think they used his hand
as a paintbrush.

04:33.838 --> 04:36.145
♪

04:36.188 --> 04:38.452
Guy's name was David Page, 45.

04:38.495 --> 04:40.628
He did okay,
middle-manager-of-a-bank type,

04:40.671 --> 04:43.457
decent living, little bit
of a loner, divorced, no kids.

04:43.500 --> 04:44.806
Neighbor said he lived
by himself,

04:44.849 --> 04:46.938
but was a nice enough guy.
- Who called it in?

04:46.982 --> 04:48.418
- The housecleaners
called it in.

04:48.462 --> 04:49.419
They have a key.
They let themselves in.

04:49.463 --> 04:50.725
It's a weekly thing.

04:50.768 --> 04:51.900
Victim's usually at work
when they get here,

04:51.943 --> 04:53.771
but this time...
- Uh, the ME's prelim

04:53.815 --> 04:55.991
says that Page was strangled
sometime last night.

04:56.034 --> 04:57.209
Weapon was a rope.

04:57.253 --> 04:58.950
- Yo, Sarge,
we got the victim's wallet.

04:58.994 --> 04:59.951
We got his cell phone.

04:59.995 --> 05:01.083
The money's still
in the wallet.

05:01.126 --> 05:02.345
He's got a few decent watches
upstairs

05:02.389 --> 05:03.781
that we can inventory,
but there's no signs

05:03.825 --> 05:05.870
of forced entry, so it
obviously wasn't a robbery.

05:05.914 --> 05:07.132
- Someone sure wanted
this guy dead

05:07.176 --> 05:08.743
and to send a message
while they're at it.

05:08.786 --> 05:11.223
- All right, we got some idea
of what it isn't.

05:11.267 --> 05:13.661
Let's figure out what it is.

05:16.403 --> 05:18.013
- Hey.

05:20.189 --> 05:21.321
You took this job?

05:21.364 --> 05:22.626
- Yeah, sorry.

05:22.670 --> 05:23.932
- No, it's not about sorries.

05:23.975 --> 05:25.760
I'm just trying to--

05:25.803 --> 05:28.328
You know?
- I know, I know.

05:28.371 --> 05:29.329
- Well, listen, it's time.

05:29.372 --> 05:31.983
We gotta go to court.

05:32.027 --> 05:33.855
- Okay.

05:36.161 --> 05:39.730
- So you were a bit
of a miracle, Mr. Morris.

05:39.774 --> 05:40.905
- [laughs]

05:40.949 --> 05:44.561
A miracle
suggests divine intervention.

05:44.605 --> 05:46.346
With respect
to the man upstairs,

05:46.389 --> 05:48.130
I worked for mine.

05:48.173 --> 05:49.436
- [laughs]

05:49.479 --> 05:52.482
- Um...

05:52.526 --> 05:55.703
The men in my family...

05:57.357 --> 06:01.709
I had six months, tops--behind
bars or in the ground.

06:01.752 --> 06:03.580
- Except...
- I got out.

06:03.624 --> 06:06.366
Got a scholarship
after high school.

06:06.409 --> 06:08.455
Engineering program at Hamburg.

06:08.498 --> 06:09.804
- Germany?
- Yes.

06:09.847 --> 06:11.980
Yes, built bridges and canals
all around Europe

06:12.023 --> 06:15.636
for the past 20 years.
Um, met my wife there.

06:15.679 --> 06:17.812
- No children of your own?

06:20.641 --> 06:22.730
- We were not able.

06:25.297 --> 06:27.909
- You moved back to Chicago?

06:27.952 --> 06:30.694
- About six months ago,
a headhunter found me.

06:30.738 --> 06:32.522
Brought me back home.

06:32.566 --> 06:35.177
- And that's when you learned
about Makayla?

06:35.220 --> 06:38.180
- First I heard the name, yeah.

06:38.223 --> 06:40.835
Uh--
[exhales deeply]

06:40.878 --> 06:43.098
Look, I-I'm sure

06:43.141 --> 06:45.709
that Ms. Burgess is
a good person.

06:45.753 --> 06:48.538
And Linda and I are grateful
for you

06:48.582 --> 06:50.410
for taking Makayla in.

06:50.453 --> 06:52.455
[somber music]

06:52.499 --> 06:55.980
What this girl's
been through...

06:56.024 --> 07:00.507
I just--I believe in my heart
that she should be with family.

07:00.550 --> 07:03.771
Real--real family.

07:03.814 --> 07:05.990
- One last question,
Mr. Morris.

07:06.034 --> 07:08.558
When you first learned about
Makayla's story--

07:08.602 --> 07:10.908
where she's living now--

07:10.952 --> 07:15.739
did you ever think about it
in racial terms?

07:15.783 --> 07:18.655
- You mean, did I ever wonder
whether it was best

07:18.699 --> 07:21.745
for a Black girl
to be raised by a white cop

07:21.789 --> 07:24.835
in the city of Chicago?

07:24.879 --> 07:26.271
- Yes.

07:26.315 --> 07:30.058
That.

07:30.101 --> 07:35.411
♪

07:35.455 --> 07:37.282
- No.

07:37.326 --> 07:44.246
♪

07:51.514 --> 07:53.647
- So how'd it go in there?

07:53.690 --> 07:56.171
- Uncle Theo knows how
to work a room.

07:56.214 --> 07:57.520
- So where are we?

07:57.564 --> 07:59.000
- Toxicology report says there
was a high dose

07:59.043 --> 08:02.046
of phenobarbital in the scotch
David Page was drinking.

08:02.090 --> 08:04.527
- Page would've been lethargic
by the time he was killed.

08:04.571 --> 08:06.529
Comatose?
- Yeah, we broke into the DMS

08:06.573 --> 08:07.791
on Page's WhatsApp.

08:07.835 --> 08:08.923
He's been a pill-popper
for a long time.

08:08.966 --> 08:10.185
He's talking
about "rims and tires."

08:10.228 --> 08:11.839
We're guessing that's Oxy
and Percocet.

08:11.882 --> 08:14.102
- Guy was alone in the world
looking to numb out?

08:14.145 --> 08:17.061
- But then, Page changed
his tune about a week ago.

08:17.105 --> 08:17.888
No more chill pills.

08:17.932 --> 08:19.020
Page was looking to go up.

08:19.063 --> 08:20.543
He starts referencing
the "Big C"

08:20.587 --> 08:21.805
in those DMs.

08:21.849 --> 08:23.633
Coke.
Bigger money.

08:23.677 --> 08:25.417
- Then on Sunday,
three days before

08:25.461 --> 08:27.550
Page was killed, he's haggling
about money with a dealer.

08:27.594 --> 08:28.725
Dealer was not having it.

08:28.769 --> 08:30.118
- Dealer's burner triangulates

08:30.161 --> 08:32.294
to a block claimed
by the SL Boyz.

08:32.337 --> 08:35.558
In the DMs, Page refers
to the dealer as "Sin."

08:35.602 --> 08:37.386
The name popped
in the alias database.

08:37.429 --> 08:38.822
"Sin" is short for "Sinister."

08:38.866 --> 08:40.258
His real name is Cesar Altuve.

08:40.302 --> 08:42.086
- This guy is a documented
shot-caller.

08:42.130 --> 08:43.479
He deals pills.
He deals coke.

08:43.523 --> 08:44.654
He's got a violent sheet.

08:44.698 --> 08:46.917
- Bring him in.
Let me talk to him.

08:46.961 --> 08:48.528
- I said, "Call me a lawyer."

08:48.571 --> 08:51.792
- He's gonna tell you
the same thing I'm telling you.

08:54.272 --> 08:57.275
We found an entire pharmacy
on you when we picked you up.

08:57.319 --> 09:00.191
That's more than enough
to send you downstate.

09:00.235 --> 09:03.586
That's even if we don't connect
you to David Page's murder.

09:06.241 --> 09:07.808
Take a look at these.

09:07.851 --> 09:11.376
Friend of mine from the DEA
loaned them to me.

09:11.420 --> 09:13.727
It's El Salvador.

09:13.770 --> 09:16.904
Soldados Locos,
your ancestral gang.

09:16.947 --> 09:19.863
Turns out that's what they do
to guys who don't pay.

09:19.907 --> 09:21.517
- I didn't kill him.

09:21.561 --> 09:23.171
- You were beefin' over money.

09:23.214 --> 09:24.215
- [laughs]
No.

09:24.259 --> 09:25.347
- No?

09:25.390 --> 09:26.914
- He just got in deeper
than usual.

09:26.957 --> 09:28.611
We were working it out, man.

09:28.655 --> 09:29.699
That's all.

09:29.743 --> 09:32.180
- Deeper how?

09:32.223 --> 09:35.400
- His thing's popping $5 pills.
- Hmm.

09:35.444 --> 09:39.622
- Entertaining a new girl,
that's a whole new price point.

09:39.666 --> 09:42.407
- What new girl?

09:42.451 --> 09:44.235
- Some girl.

09:44.279 --> 09:45.628
She wanted to party.

09:45.672 --> 09:47.543
Powder.

09:47.587 --> 09:49.066
[knock at door]

09:49.110 --> 09:51.286
- Sarge?

09:51.329 --> 09:52.940
- What?

09:52.983 --> 09:55.203
- We got another one.

09:55.246 --> 09:57.509
[low tense music]

09:57.553 --> 10:00.338
[indistinct police
radio chatter]

10:00.382 --> 10:01.862
- So a meter man found that.

10:01.905 --> 10:03.385
Crime lab is rolling in.

10:03.428 --> 10:04.516
- Anyone been inside?

10:04.560 --> 10:05.735
- No, sir.
Waiting on you.

10:05.779 --> 10:08.042
- [coughs]
Christ.

10:08.085 --> 10:09.739
- All right, go.

10:09.783 --> 10:13.656
♪

10:13.700 --> 10:16.441
- [gags]

10:16.485 --> 10:18.487
- Oh, my God.

10:18.530 --> 10:25.625
♪

10:27.583 --> 10:29.280
- I'll go check upstairs.

10:32.806 --> 10:35.765
[somber music]

10:35.809 --> 10:42.293
♪

10:42.337 --> 10:43.686
- This one got messy.

10:43.730 --> 10:46.689
Look at his leg.

10:46.733 --> 10:49.083
- Basement's clear.

10:49.126 --> 10:50.737
- There's another
half-finished cocktail

10:50.780 --> 10:52.477
on the nightstand up there.

10:52.521 --> 10:54.784
- Okay, so...

10:54.828 --> 10:57.831
he realizes he's been drugged.

10:57.874 --> 10:59.702
Makes a run for it.
Legs give out.

10:59.746 --> 11:00.703
He falls down the stairs.

11:00.747 --> 11:03.140
Killer catches up
with him here.

11:03.184 --> 11:06.535
- Yeah, well, this does not
look like gang violence.

11:06.578 --> 11:09.059
♪

11:09.103 --> 11:11.845
We got a serial killer.

11:11.888 --> 11:13.324
♪

11:16.719 --> 11:16.937
.

11:16.980 --> 11:18.982
- Second victim's Gus Thompson,
48.

11:19.026 --> 11:20.418
ME said he'd been dead
for a week.

11:20.462 --> 11:22.116
- Yeah, same deal as
our first victim, David Page.

11:22.159 --> 11:23.639
Phenobarbital in his drink.

11:23.683 --> 11:25.467
Strangled,
then his hand was cut off.

11:25.510 --> 11:27.991
- Thompson's a middle-manager,
working stiff, lonely,

11:28.035 --> 11:29.558
no family--same there too.

11:29.601 --> 11:30.951
- But no sign our victims know
each other.

11:30.994 --> 11:32.430
Two men from two different
sides of the city.

11:32.474 --> 11:33.562
- We got another one.

11:33.605 --> 11:36.783
Joel McCall, 55,
killed six weeks ago.

11:36.826 --> 11:38.959
Drugged, strangled,
his hand cut off.

11:39.002 --> 11:40.221
- Case didn't pop before?

11:40.264 --> 11:41.309
- It's not ours.

11:41.352 --> 11:42.614
Belongs to Des Plaines PD.

11:42.658 --> 11:43.920
I had to find it on ViCAP.

11:43.964 --> 11:46.314
And just like the others,
no defensive wounds,

11:46.357 --> 11:47.794
nothing disturbed in the home.

11:47.837 --> 11:52.146
And this one, his blood was
used to write "Leave us."

11:52.189 --> 11:54.365
- Us?
- Yeah, that part's weird,

11:54.409 --> 11:55.715
among other things.

11:55.758 --> 11:57.151
I arranged for you guys
to head over there.

11:57.194 --> 11:58.543
They're copying case files.

11:58.587 --> 12:00.807
They even offered a couple
of their homicide cops

12:00.850 --> 12:02.156
if you're interested.

12:02.199 --> 12:04.158
Look at me making friends.

12:04.201 --> 12:05.550
- Thanks, Trudy.

12:05.594 --> 12:07.509
Now listen, these men were
targeted for a reason.

12:07.552 --> 12:10.164
These messages,
they mean something.

12:10.207 --> 12:12.993
We find the why,
we'll find the who.

12:13.036 --> 12:14.472
Dig in.

12:15.996 --> 12:17.258
- I'm gonna head up
to Des Plaines right now.

12:17.301 --> 12:18.389
- Yeah,
I'm gonna come with you.

12:18.433 --> 12:19.608
- No, no, no.
- Gabby can stay late.

12:19.651 --> 12:20.914
She can stay late.
- I'll take it alone.

12:20.957 --> 12:22.350
Chances are I'll get
all the way up there

12:22.393 --> 12:23.786
and I don't find out anything
anyway.

12:23.830 --> 12:25.353
You go be with Mack.

12:25.396 --> 12:26.920
You guys need each other.
- [sighs]

12:26.963 --> 12:29.923
[somber music]

12:29.966 --> 12:34.797
♪

12:34.841 --> 12:36.233
[door clicks open]

12:36.277 --> 12:37.713
Hello?
- Hey.

12:37.757 --> 12:39.106
Just cleaning up.
- No, no, no.

12:39.149 --> 12:41.804
Gabby, please, I'll do that.

12:41.848 --> 12:43.284
[laughs]

12:43.327 --> 12:44.372
Hello.

12:44.415 --> 12:45.373
What'd you have for dinner?

12:45.416 --> 12:47.114
- We ordered chicken parm.

12:47.157 --> 12:48.550
Saved some for you.
- Thank you.

12:48.593 --> 12:50.813
- And I had six peas
and three carrots.

12:50.857 --> 12:52.423
- [laughs]
Six peas and three carrots.

12:52.467 --> 12:55.818
But who's counting, right?
- Got a bit of a project going.

12:55.862 --> 12:57.559
- Okay.

12:57.602 --> 13:00.214
- Me and Jasmine--
- Jasmine and I.

13:00.257 --> 13:01.955
- That's what I said.

13:01.998 --> 13:04.827
Me and Jasmine are
in a school skit tomorrow.

13:04.871 --> 13:07.308
Our hair's gonna be
the exact same.

13:07.351 --> 13:09.614
♪

13:09.658 --> 13:12.356
- Picked up the beads, but...

13:12.400 --> 13:19.537
♪

13:21.496 --> 13:23.977
- All right, um...

13:24.020 --> 13:25.674
Can you hand me a bead?

13:25.717 --> 13:26.762
- Sure.

13:29.286 --> 13:30.287
- Okay.

13:30.331 --> 13:31.767
[band snaps]

13:31.811 --> 13:34.857
[beads rattling]

13:34.901 --> 13:36.903
Oop.
[sighs]

13:36.946 --> 13:39.688
Okay, well, it's something
like this, right?

13:39.731 --> 13:42.212
- Um, I don't think so.

13:42.256 --> 13:44.432
♪

13:44.475 --> 13:46.260
- Okay, I'll try again.

13:46.303 --> 13:48.958
- Well, it's only hair.

13:49.002 --> 13:51.961
[beads falling]

13:53.963 --> 13:57.401
What are we gonna do?

13:57.445 --> 13:59.273
- We're gonna call
your Uncle Kevin.

13:59.316 --> 14:01.884
- Okay.
- Okay.

14:01.928 --> 14:06.149
♪

14:06.193 --> 14:08.238
Good news is, you can lord
this over me forever.

14:08.282 --> 14:09.370
- And you know I will.

14:09.413 --> 14:10.806
What's up, Queen?

14:10.850 --> 14:12.286
Yeah, yeah,
come on in.

14:12.329 --> 14:13.678
[laughter]

14:13.722 --> 14:14.984
You remember my Auntie Jane?

14:15.028 --> 14:16.116
- Hey, Jane.

14:16.159 --> 14:17.421
Do you remember, Makayla?

14:17.465 --> 14:19.336
We met Jane
at Jordan's birthday party.

14:19.380 --> 14:20.468
- Yeah, I remember.

14:20.511 --> 14:23.471
- Let me see my VIP client.

14:23.514 --> 14:25.125
Black hair is its own thing.

14:25.168 --> 14:26.909
Its own beautiful thing.

14:26.953 --> 14:28.258
Come on, baby.
We got this.

14:28.302 --> 14:31.392
Come on.

14:31.435 --> 14:33.176
- Oh, Jane, beads.

14:33.220 --> 14:34.569
- Thank you.

14:34.612 --> 14:35.744
- It's actually not that bad.

14:35.787 --> 14:38.616
- Shut up.

14:42.272 --> 14:44.231
I mean, I'll hand it to him.

14:44.274 --> 14:46.755
Makayla's uncle found a way
to make this custody case

14:46.798 --> 14:49.758
about race while denying
he was making it about race.

14:49.801 --> 14:51.760
- Okay, Theo
came to fight, huh?

14:51.803 --> 14:53.631
- Oh, yeah.
- Well, what'd the judge say?

14:53.675 --> 14:55.111
- She smiled.
She got it.

14:59.594 --> 15:02.553
Is this okay?

15:02.597 --> 15:05.426
Black kid, white cop,
this city.

15:05.469 --> 15:07.819
♪

15:07.863 --> 15:08.951
- I mean, I'm not gonna
act like

15:08.995 --> 15:12.694
this is
some colorblind fairy tale.

15:12.737 --> 15:15.697
But what you and Kev have got
is solid as hell.

15:15.740 --> 15:17.177
- Yeah, I know,
there's truth there.

15:17.220 --> 15:18.961
I just...

15:19.005 --> 15:20.441
It hurt to hear in court.

15:20.484 --> 15:24.575
- But, Burgess,
you are good for her.

15:24.619 --> 15:26.142
You know that.

15:26.186 --> 15:28.623
- I do.

15:28.666 --> 15:32.018
But to have to prove it...

15:32.061 --> 15:33.976
- Ta-da!

15:34.020 --> 15:35.369
- [laughs]

15:35.412 --> 15:36.892
- Oh, my, turn around!

15:36.936 --> 15:38.372
Turn around.
Let me see the whole thing.

15:38.415 --> 15:39.286
[squeals]
- Look at that.

15:39.329 --> 15:41.418
- [squeals]

15:41.462 --> 15:43.290
Thank you.

15:43.333 --> 15:45.074
You look beautiful.

15:47.337 --> 15:48.382
- Well, we got lucky.

15:48.425 --> 15:49.818
Got a hit in Des Plaines.

15:49.861 --> 15:51.776
Traffic cams got a good view
of the victim's home.

15:51.820 --> 15:53.213
Rubber-bullet squad up there

15:53.256 --> 15:54.779
was told the traffic cam
was down, so they missed it.

15:54.823 --> 15:57.695
Now this right here,
it's 4:12 p.m.

15:57.739 --> 15:59.959
That's two hours before
Joel McCall was found dead.

16:00.002 --> 16:02.439
- This woman leaves the
victim's house, walking fast.

16:02.483 --> 16:03.875
She gets into
a Volkswagen Scirocco.

16:03.919 --> 16:06.139
- And right here you get
a decent view of the driver.

16:06.182 --> 16:07.836
Another female.
- So you're thinking

16:07.879 --> 16:09.272
that's the woman
Altuve mentioned?

16:09.316 --> 16:10.795
The one David Page was seeing?

16:10.839 --> 16:12.145
- We haven't found a trace
of her yet,

16:12.188 --> 16:13.581
but maybe that's how
they lured him in.

16:13.624 --> 16:14.625
- So a VW pulls out.

16:14.669 --> 16:15.757
We got the plates.

16:15.800 --> 16:16.932
Comes back
to a Daniel Williams.

16:16.976 --> 16:17.889
- Now here's where
it gets good.

16:17.933 --> 16:19.239
Daniel doesn't have a sheet,

16:19.282 --> 16:20.892
but he's got a sister.

16:20.936 --> 16:21.850
Jackie Williams.

16:21.893 --> 16:24.244
She's 24.

16:24.287 --> 16:25.680
[intense music]

16:25.723 --> 16:27.290
- That's a dead match
for our driver.

16:27.334 --> 16:28.552
- LKA on Cottage Grove.

16:28.596 --> 16:29.553
- Nice work.

16:29.597 --> 16:32.121
Hit it.

16:32.165 --> 16:35.255
[suspenseful music]

16:35.298 --> 16:38.432
♪

16:38.475 --> 16:41.609
- I got the back.

16:41.652 --> 16:45.091
[music intensifies]

16:45.134 --> 16:47.267
♪

16:47.310 --> 16:49.269
- Chicago PD!

16:49.312 --> 16:52.968
♪

16:53.012 --> 16:55.623
- Move.

16:55.666 --> 17:02.021
♪

17:02.064 --> 17:04.284
- It's clear.

17:04.327 --> 17:11.247
♪

17:24.043 --> 17:26.262
- Looks like someone's home.

17:28.090 --> 17:29.570
- Dan Williams?

17:29.613 --> 17:30.745
Police, let me see your hands.
- Whoa!

17:30.788 --> 17:33.095
- Keep your hands
where I can see them.

17:33.139 --> 17:34.444
- Does this mean--

17:34.488 --> 17:36.011
You found her?

17:36.055 --> 17:36.838
- Found who?

17:36.881 --> 17:38.709
- Jackie, my sister.

17:38.753 --> 17:41.973
Is she with him?

17:42.017 --> 17:43.323
Is she?

17:43.366 --> 17:44.585
- We don't know
who you're talking about, Dan.

17:44.628 --> 17:45.542
With who?

17:45.586 --> 17:46.674
- Micah.

17:46.717 --> 17:50.417
With him, with the cult.

17:50.460 --> 17:52.375
Isn't that why you're here?

17:52.419 --> 17:55.335
[tense music]

17:55.378 --> 17:56.771
♪

18:00.253 --> 18:00.427
.

18:00.470 --> 18:02.342
- So what do you mean, "cult"?
- I don't know

18:02.385 --> 18:03.778
if that's the right word.

18:03.821 --> 18:06.520
Can you just tell me,
is Jackie okay?

18:06.563 --> 18:08.609
Is she all right?
- We don't know, Dan.

18:08.652 --> 18:09.914
Can you tell us
what happened to her?

18:09.958 --> 18:12.047
- Look, she's just been
having a hard time.

18:12.091 --> 18:13.222
I mean, she always has.

18:13.266 --> 18:16.356
But last couple years,
she lost her job.

18:16.399 --> 18:18.184
We don't have any other family,
any money.

18:18.227 --> 18:19.228
She was just desperate.

18:19.272 --> 18:20.882
- And that's when
she met Micah?

18:20.925 --> 18:21.883
- Yeah.

18:21.926 --> 18:23.711
He calmed her down.

18:23.754 --> 18:25.452
Then she started
talking about him weird.

18:25.495 --> 18:28.150
Like he wasn't a friend,
boyfriend.

18:28.194 --> 18:30.152
- Okay.

18:30.196 --> 18:31.632
What was he?

18:31.675 --> 18:33.938
- Like a teacher.

18:33.982 --> 18:35.679
Guy lives with other women.

18:35.723 --> 18:37.725
Asked Jackie to move in
and then...

18:37.768 --> 18:42.730
I told her this guy's no good,
but she couldn't hear it.

18:42.773 --> 18:46.168
I think she started
using again.

18:46.212 --> 18:49.084
Cut me out.

18:49.128 --> 18:52.305
And then she was gone.

18:52.348 --> 18:54.176
- Recognize this woman?

18:54.220 --> 18:55.743
- No.

18:55.786 --> 18:57.788
- What about her?

18:57.832 --> 18:59.964
- Yeah, that's Jackie.

19:00.008 --> 19:01.140
And my old car.
What--

19:01.183 --> 19:02.750
Why?

19:02.793 --> 19:05.927
[dark music]

19:05.970 --> 19:08.059
What'd they do?

19:08.103 --> 19:10.279
♪

19:10.323 --> 19:12.020
- This is from Jackie Williams'
social media.

19:12.063 --> 19:13.891
It was deleted,
but we were able to recover it.

19:13.935 --> 19:16.024
- Okay, so that's Jackie.

19:16.067 --> 19:18.722
That is the woman who exited
the house in Des Plaines.

19:18.766 --> 19:20.463
All these women,
they look undernourished,

19:20.507 --> 19:22.596
off the streets,
possible drug use.

19:22.639 --> 19:25.338
And that is Micah Thurman,
44 years old.

19:25.381 --> 19:28.993
- We are going to build
a life together.

19:29.037 --> 19:33.215
You will be loved, safe,
but this won't come free.

19:33.259 --> 19:36.218
You must choose this family.

19:36.262 --> 19:38.133
♪

19:38.177 --> 19:41.267
You must choose me.

19:41.310 --> 19:46.228
Now this is going
to require discipline.

19:46.272 --> 19:49.275
Accountability.

19:49.318 --> 19:50.580
But you're home.
[keyboard clacks]

19:50.624 --> 19:52.452
- Micah Thurman,
he's a grifter.

19:52.495 --> 19:54.236
A conman.
He's been on the run for years.

19:54.280 --> 19:56.238
Got numerous civil
and criminal charges,

19:56.282 --> 19:57.892
two-bit fraud, check-bouncing.

19:57.935 --> 19:59.633
He's got a domestic
from a decade ago.

19:59.676 --> 20:00.938
- Mm.
- And these women are trying

20:00.982 --> 20:02.244
to make a family with him?

20:02.288 --> 20:03.245
- I mean, he knows
exactly what they need

20:03.289 --> 20:04.725
to replace fear with hope.

20:04.768 --> 20:07.293
- It'll take discipline,
but you have to do what I say.

20:07.336 --> 20:09.251
- [sighs]
What if they would do anything

20:09.295 --> 20:10.600
that he said
to be in his family?

20:10.644 --> 20:12.080
What if they would
kill for him?

20:12.123 --> 20:13.951
- Mm, so where's Micah now?

20:13.995 --> 20:15.039
- We don't know.

20:15.083 --> 20:16.476
He's off the grid.

20:16.519 --> 20:18.260
Creditors haven't been able
to find him in years.

20:18.304 --> 20:19.783
He doesn't have a cell phone.

20:19.827 --> 20:21.089
No utilities in his name.

20:21.132 --> 20:22.960
- Only connection
we actually have is Jackie.

20:23.004 --> 20:24.875
And we threw a BOLO
out there on her Scirocco,

20:24.919 --> 20:26.007
but we ain't got a hit yet.

20:26.050 --> 20:27.487
- We do have one more thread
on her.

20:27.530 --> 20:30.185
It's not much, but she swipes
her Link card once a week

20:30.229 --> 20:31.360
at a market off Hamlin.

20:31.404 --> 20:32.405
- Okay, good.

20:32.448 --> 20:33.580
That's a string to pull.

20:33.623 --> 20:36.365
Do it.

20:43.633 --> 20:46.288
- Nah, maybe this is a bust.

20:46.332 --> 20:48.247
- Just gotta ride it out.

20:55.210 --> 20:56.342
- There.

20:56.385 --> 20:58.561
I can't make out
the plate though.

20:58.605 --> 21:02.173
- Guys, we got a VW
north side of the lot.

21:02.217 --> 21:03.871
[tense music]

21:03.914 --> 21:06.003
Female subject exiting
the vehicle.

21:06.047 --> 21:07.918
- Any signs of Micah
or the other women?

21:07.962 --> 21:10.051
- Negative, she's alone.

21:10.094 --> 21:11.270
- That's her.

21:11.313 --> 21:12.532
It's a positive
on Jackie Williams.

21:12.575 --> 21:14.142
Let's move.
- All right.

21:14.185 --> 21:15.186
We're gonna cover the back.

21:15.230 --> 21:22.585
♪

21:23.412 --> 21:25.849
[indistinct overhead
announcements]

21:28.156 --> 21:30.550
- Jackie?
Jackie Williams?

21:30.593 --> 21:32.465
Chicago police,
we just wanna talk to you.

21:32.508 --> 21:36.077
♪

21:36.120 --> 21:39.341
Jackie, hey.

21:39.385 --> 21:40.429
Hey.
- Jackie?

21:40.473 --> 21:42.344
- Stop running.
- [grunts]

21:42.388 --> 21:45.391
[screaming]
No!

21:45.434 --> 21:47.088
[shrieking]
- Take it easy.

21:47.131 --> 21:48.263
- Jackie.
- No!

21:48.307 --> 21:50.047
- Take a breath.
- No, no!

21:50.091 --> 21:52.441
Please get off!
No!

21:52.485 --> 21:54.313
- [panting]
- [groaning]

22:00.101 --> 22:02.277
- Okay, Jackie,
I'm gonna uncuff you now.

22:02.321 --> 22:04.105
And I need you to not do
what you did at the market.

22:04.148 --> 22:06.020
You understand?

22:06.063 --> 22:07.717
[cuffs clinking]

22:16.465 --> 22:18.554
All right.

22:18.598 --> 22:20.077
Is this you in this Volkswagen?

22:20.121 --> 22:22.341
That's your brother's car.
We talked to him.

22:22.384 --> 22:24.343
Your brother Dan,
do you remember him?

22:30.349 --> 22:33.613
What about this photo?

22:33.656 --> 22:35.615
Who's this person?
Who got into the car with you?

22:40.184 --> 22:42.535
All right.

22:42.578 --> 22:43.710
Why this house?

22:43.753 --> 22:45.320
Did you know the man
who lived there?

22:45.364 --> 22:47.366
Why him?

22:52.109 --> 22:55.417
Hey, where'd you go
when you left Des Plaines?

22:55.461 --> 22:58.638
Did you go to Micah?

22:58.681 --> 23:00.422
Yeah?
Where is Micah?

23:00.466 --> 23:02.555
[tense music]

23:02.598 --> 23:05.253
- He's with me.

23:05.296 --> 23:06.602
Right now.

23:06.646 --> 23:09.475
- Oh.
- Not actually here.

23:09.518 --> 23:12.347
I'm not crazy.
I don't see ghosts.

23:12.391 --> 23:13.740
- Good.

23:13.783 --> 23:15.742
- We were on the edge
of a cliff when he found us.

23:15.785 --> 23:18.222
Saved us.
Made us family.

23:18.266 --> 23:20.877
- What'd he save you from?

23:20.921 --> 23:24.446
♪

23:24.490 --> 23:27.536
- The wobblies.

23:27.580 --> 23:30.887
- Wobblies?

23:30.931 --> 23:34.021
- [laughs]

23:34.064 --> 23:37.198
- [chuckles]

23:37.241 --> 23:39.200
- That's what we call it.

23:39.243 --> 23:41.115
Fear.

23:44.423 --> 23:47.600
But we're safe now.

23:47.643 --> 23:50.080
Part of something bigger
than ourselves.

23:50.124 --> 23:51.517
Might not look
like a family to you,

23:51.560 --> 23:53.780
but it feels like one to us.

23:56.130 --> 23:58.088
You got the wobblies too?

24:00.656 --> 24:03.616
- No, we're not gonna talk
about me, Jackie.

24:03.659 --> 24:05.487
- I can see it.

24:05.531 --> 24:09.230
♪

24:09.273 --> 24:10.971
You're scared.

24:16.324 --> 24:18.500
Micah can help you.

24:18.544 --> 24:20.502
He can take it away.

24:20.546 --> 24:23.070
- Three men were murdered,
Jackie.

24:23.113 --> 24:26.247
And you were there
for at least one of them.

24:26.290 --> 24:28.554
Yeah.

24:28.597 --> 24:30.425
Do you get what's happening?

24:30.469 --> 24:34.951
Do you understand the stakes?

24:34.995 --> 24:40.391
♪

24:40.435 --> 24:41.567
[door opens]

24:45.962 --> 24:48.704
- If we don't get her talking,
we're dead in the water.

24:48.748 --> 24:49.923
I mean, we got nothing
on Micah,

24:49.966 --> 24:51.881
no leads on
that other female offender.

24:51.925 --> 24:53.404
- And nothing connecting
any of them

24:53.448 --> 24:56.538
to any of our victims either.

24:56.582 --> 24:59.454
- I can get her to break.

24:59.498 --> 25:02.152
I can feel it.

25:02.196 --> 25:04.067
Deep down, this girl knows
she's hanging on to something

25:04.111 --> 25:05.155
that isn't really there.

25:05.199 --> 25:07.549
It's not real.

25:07.593 --> 25:10.770
Just need to find the right way
to tear it down.

25:10.813 --> 25:13.337
- Go ahead,
put her on ice for the night.

25:13.381 --> 25:14.556
Just dig back in tomorrow.

25:14.600 --> 25:16.515
- Okay.

25:19.518 --> 25:23.217
[phone vibrates]

25:26.176 --> 25:28.222
This is Kim.

25:28.265 --> 25:31.181
[somber music]

25:31.225 --> 25:36.447
♪

25:36.491 --> 25:38.362
- Hey.

25:38.406 --> 25:40.016
There you are.
What's going on?

25:40.060 --> 25:44.325
♪

25:44.368 --> 25:46.675
What happened?

25:46.719 --> 25:48.764
- The judge, she's allowing
Theo's lawyers

25:48.808 --> 25:50.331
to access my medical records.

25:50.374 --> 25:51.506
- From when you got hurt?

25:51.550 --> 25:53.160
- And to depose my doctors

25:53.203 --> 25:54.553
and to access
my personnel file--

25:54.596 --> 25:56.076
- Well, what does that mean?

25:56.119 --> 25:58.644
- That's their case.
It's their argument.

25:58.687 --> 26:00.820
I can't possibly offer Makayla
a stable home

26:00.863 --> 26:02.343
because I almost died.

26:02.386 --> 26:05.346
And I was offered a desk job
and I came back to this.

26:05.389 --> 26:06.695
I chose this.
- Kim.

26:06.739 --> 26:07.740
- Oh, my God,
what if they're right though?

26:07.783 --> 26:09.437
What if I'm not good
for Makayla?

26:09.480 --> 26:12.832
- No, no.
You stop that now.

26:12.875 --> 26:15.835
Stop it.

26:15.878 --> 26:17.967
- But they're trying to prove
how close I came to dying

26:18.011 --> 26:20.143
in order to--
[sighs]

26:20.187 --> 26:23.233
To take away the one thing
that kept me alive.

26:23.277 --> 26:24.234
- They cannot do that.

26:24.278 --> 26:25.758
- They can and they are.

26:25.801 --> 26:27.977
We're gonna lose her, Adam.

26:28.021 --> 26:31.372
Just--we're gonna lose her.

26:31.415 --> 26:37.683
♪

26:40.773 --> 26:41.208
.

26:41.251 --> 26:42.122
[door clicks open]

26:45.516 --> 26:49.390
[cuffs clinking]

26:51.392 --> 26:54.743
- Micah lied to you.

26:54.787 --> 26:57.267
- He doesn't lie.
- Okay.

26:57.311 --> 26:58.660
That's David Page.

26:58.704 --> 27:00.619
Before you came on the scene,
Micah bought a car.

27:00.662 --> 27:01.750
He couldn't keep up
with the payments,

27:01.794 --> 27:03.056
and he fought the bank

27:03.099 --> 27:04.535
until he got
a mid-level manager

27:04.579 --> 27:05.841
who told him
his hands were tied.

27:05.885 --> 27:07.408
He had to repo the car.

27:07.451 --> 27:09.628
That manager was--do you see
that signature right there?

27:09.671 --> 27:10.977
David Page.

27:11.020 --> 27:12.631
The others were the same.
There's Gus Thompson.

27:12.674 --> 27:14.371
He owned a couple
of lending stores.

27:14.415 --> 27:16.896
He gave Micah a crappy loan
at a crappy rate.

27:16.939 --> 27:17.940
Micah couldn't pay it off.

27:17.984 --> 27:19.072
It drove him deeper into debt.

27:19.115 --> 27:20.900
- That's not true.
- It is.

27:20.943 --> 27:23.685
Then there is Joel McCall.

27:23.729 --> 27:25.295
He turned down
Micah's application

27:25.339 --> 27:27.428
for a second mortgage,
and Micah lost his house.

27:27.471 --> 27:30.126
This was years ago and you
were still in high school.

27:30.170 --> 27:32.172
So all these guys,

27:32.215 --> 27:34.000
they were just doing their job.

27:34.043 --> 27:37.220
Regular men with friends,
family, people who loved them.

27:41.224 --> 27:42.225
- No.

27:42.269 --> 27:43.444
- Yes.
- Micah told us.

27:43.487 --> 27:45.881
- What'd he tell you?

27:45.925 --> 27:47.187
- They were after our family.

27:47.230 --> 27:48.710
- No.

27:48.754 --> 27:51.452
They didn't even know
you existed.

27:51.495 --> 27:54.237
They just--they made Micah mad
a long time ago.

27:54.281 --> 27:56.196
That's it.
That's it, Jackie.

27:56.239 --> 27:58.502
That's all this ever was.

28:00.200 --> 28:02.202
- No.

28:02.245 --> 28:03.899
♪

28:03.943 --> 28:07.207
No.

28:07.250 --> 28:08.730
No...

28:08.774 --> 28:10.906
♪

28:10.950 --> 28:14.127
[crying]

28:16.651 --> 28:20.655
- You were right about me.
I've been scared.

28:20.699 --> 28:25.312
♪

28:25.355 --> 28:30.230
I get why you'd reach out
for something like this.

28:30.273 --> 28:32.101
[sighs]

28:32.145 --> 28:36.758
♪

28:36.802 --> 28:41.197
But the thing is,
is that Micah used you.

28:41.241 --> 28:44.810
- No.
- Yeah.

28:44.853 --> 28:47.638
But you can fight him.

28:47.682 --> 28:48.639
You can help me.

28:48.683 --> 28:49.728
You could help me
make this right.

28:49.771 --> 28:51.207
- [sniffs]

28:51.251 --> 28:58.345
♪

29:00.521 --> 29:04.264
I never hurt anybody.

29:04.307 --> 29:05.656
- Okay.

29:05.700 --> 29:08.268
- And I never went inside
anywhere.

29:08.311 --> 29:09.748
- That's good.

29:09.791 --> 29:12.576
I believe you.

29:12.620 --> 29:13.795
That means we can work
together.

29:13.839 --> 29:16.406
And if you help me,
I'll do everything I can

29:16.450 --> 29:19.888
to make sure you go free
at the end of this.

29:19.932 --> 29:21.890
You can go home, Jackie.

29:21.934 --> 29:26.068
♪

29:26.112 --> 29:28.679
Home to your real family.

29:28.723 --> 29:34.990
♪

29:35.034 --> 29:37.471
Our offender's name
is Jenny Valentine, 27.

29:37.514 --> 29:38.820
ID'd by Jackie.

29:38.864 --> 29:40.822
- Jenny, she's been in and out
of jail for years.

29:40.866 --> 29:43.433
Possession,
small-time sales of meth.

29:43.477 --> 29:45.479
And that's actually Jenny
in the Des Plaines video

29:45.522 --> 29:46.523
getting into the Volkswagen.

29:46.567 --> 29:47.829
- According to Jackie,

29:47.873 --> 29:49.700
Jenny murdered all three
of our victims.

29:49.744 --> 29:52.355
- Okay, but did Jackie say
if Micah ordered the kills?

29:52.399 --> 29:53.922
- She doesn't know.
Not exactly.

29:53.966 --> 29:56.011
- How's that work?

29:56.055 --> 29:57.360
- Micah fed them lies.

29:57.404 --> 29:59.188
Told them their family
was in danger,

29:59.232 --> 30:00.711
that these men hated them.

30:00.755 --> 30:02.931
She just never
specifically heard Micah

30:02.975 --> 30:04.454
tell Jenny to kill anyone.

30:04.498 --> 30:06.587
- Jackie also said she never
saw blood on Jenny.

30:06.630 --> 30:08.850
She was never explicitly told
why she was driving Jenny

30:08.894 --> 30:10.025
to these locations.

30:10.069 --> 30:11.331
- That's plenty
for a warrant on Jenny

30:11.374 --> 30:13.855
but real shaky on Micah.

30:13.899 --> 30:16.031
- I know.

30:16.075 --> 30:17.424
- Yeah, I want Micah.

30:18.817 --> 30:20.557
All right, where did they live?

30:20.601 --> 30:22.908
- Abandoned property
in Humboldt Park.

30:22.951 --> 30:25.388
- Well, we wire Jackie.
Send her back to the family.

30:25.432 --> 30:27.347
Get Micah talking.
Can she deliver?

30:27.390 --> 30:29.871
Is she stable enough?

30:29.915 --> 30:31.177
- I don't know.

30:31.220 --> 30:35.964
♪

30:36.008 --> 30:37.226
But I'd try.

30:37.270 --> 30:38.271
- All right.

30:38.314 --> 30:41.230
There we go.

30:41.274 --> 30:44.190
[suspenseful music]

30:44.233 --> 30:51.371
♪

30:58.987 --> 31:00.423
- Jackie.

31:00.467 --> 31:01.990
- Positive on Micah Thurman.

31:02.034 --> 31:04.297
- We were worried.

31:04.340 --> 31:06.908
- Just ran into a couple
of friends

31:06.952 --> 31:08.823
from my old life.

31:08.867 --> 31:12.218
They had just scored and, um,
asked if I wanted to party.

31:12.261 --> 31:15.090
I was weak.

31:15.134 --> 31:17.136
It was a mistake.

31:17.179 --> 31:18.224
- Attagirl.

31:18.267 --> 31:19.790
- I don't need them anymore.

31:19.834 --> 31:23.490
All I need is us.

31:23.533 --> 31:24.883
I missed you.

31:24.926 --> 31:28.408
[low dark music]

31:28.451 --> 31:30.062
- Jenny was worried sick.

31:30.105 --> 31:32.020
- All right, that's the first
mention of Valentine.

31:32.064 --> 31:33.630
Stay on your toes.
- Jenny thought--

31:33.674 --> 31:35.197
- Copy.
- That you...

31:35.241 --> 31:38.592
panicked because of
the nights you went driving.

31:38.635 --> 31:41.029
- Everything we did
made us safer.

31:41.073 --> 31:43.379
- We're close.

31:43.423 --> 31:46.165
- Are you ready for more,
Jackie?

31:46.208 --> 31:49.733
- What do you mean?

31:49.777 --> 31:51.779
What do you want me
to do next?

31:51.822 --> 31:56.001
- Oh, my...

31:56.044 --> 31:57.524
What happened to you?

31:57.567 --> 31:59.700
♪

31:59.743 --> 32:04.313
You're like a little deer.

32:04.357 --> 32:05.314
So frightened.

32:05.358 --> 32:07.882
[tense music]

32:07.926 --> 32:09.449
♪

32:09.492 --> 32:12.365
Let me feel your heart beat.

32:14.062 --> 32:16.325
Yes.

32:16.369 --> 32:18.023
Something's happened.

32:18.066 --> 32:21.330
♪

32:21.374 --> 32:22.331
- I'm fine.

32:22.375 --> 32:25.378
♪

32:25.421 --> 32:28.511
- Is the family in danger?

32:28.555 --> 32:30.992
Tell me what you've done,
Jackie.

32:31.036 --> 32:33.342
♪

32:33.386 --> 32:37.172
- I'm so sorry.
I'm sorry.

32:37.216 --> 32:40.349
- No.

32:40.393 --> 32:42.873
- Oh, Jackie.

32:42.917 --> 32:44.223
- We're dark.

32:44.266 --> 32:45.876
- Let's move in.
Move!

32:45.920 --> 32:47.226
We're headed to the south.

32:47.269 --> 32:50.969
Breach wherever you can,
but move in silent.

32:51.012 --> 32:53.928
[intense music]

32:53.972 --> 32:57.062
♪

32:57.105 --> 32:58.933
- We're entering north side.

32:58.977 --> 33:05.896
♪

33:21.869 --> 33:23.088
- [screams]
- Hey, stop!

33:23.131 --> 33:24.959
Stop, don't make me shoot you,
okay?

33:25.003 --> 33:26.439
I don't wanna shoot.
- [screams]

33:26.482 --> 33:28.049
- There you go.
We know everything, okay?

33:28.093 --> 33:30.269
Calm down.
We know everything!

33:30.312 --> 33:31.922
He ain't worth it.

33:31.966 --> 33:35.970
♪

33:36.014 --> 33:37.276
- Jackie?

33:37.319 --> 33:39.452
Is Micah in here?

33:39.495 --> 33:41.541
Jackie.

33:41.584 --> 33:44.065
♪

33:44.109 --> 33:45.066
Can you respond to me?

33:45.110 --> 33:47.547
- Cover me.

33:47.590 --> 33:49.331
Jackie?

33:49.375 --> 33:51.725
It's me.
Hey, look at me.

33:51.768 --> 33:54.075
You're safe.
You're good.

33:54.119 --> 33:59.037
Where's Micah?

33:59.080 --> 34:00.386
- Kim--hey, hey!

34:00.429 --> 34:05.782
♪

34:05.826 --> 34:08.220
[metal creaking]
- Chicago PD!

34:08.263 --> 34:10.004
[door slams]

34:10.048 --> 34:16.967
♪

34:27.891 --> 34:29.676
[metal creaks
and door slams shut]

34:29.719 --> 34:32.809
♪

34:36.552 --> 34:36.770
.

34:36.813 --> 34:38.337
- [panting]

34:38.380 --> 34:41.514
[suspenseful music]

34:41.557 --> 34:48.521
♪

34:54.004 --> 34:56.442
It's over, Micah!

34:56.485 --> 34:58.183
The girls,
they know who you really are.

34:58.226 --> 35:01.229
It's over.
Your family, it's over!

35:01.273 --> 35:03.971
[gunshots]

35:04.014 --> 35:11.109
♪

35:14.199 --> 35:16.026
Last chance, Micah!

35:16.070 --> 35:18.116
I'm coming for ya!

35:18.159 --> 35:23.077
♪

35:23.121 --> 35:25.688
[gunshots]

35:25.732 --> 35:27.125
[soft thud]

35:27.168 --> 35:34.219
♪

35:36.046 --> 35:38.701
[panting]

35:38.745 --> 35:41.051
[lights click on]

35:41.095 --> 35:42.183
- Kim, are you all right?

35:42.227 --> 35:44.490
- I'm okay!

35:46.318 --> 35:49.016
[soft dark music]

35:49.059 --> 35:54.891
♪

35:54.935 --> 35:56.676
- Your Honor, we're here today

35:56.719 --> 35:59.200
because
of fundamental questions

35:59.244 --> 36:02.072
about Ms. Burgess' fitness
as a mother.

36:02.116 --> 36:03.857
Makayla has seen you
with a gun in your hand.

36:03.900 --> 36:06.381
Suffers from night terrors.

36:06.425 --> 36:08.992
There seems
to be some confusion

36:09.036 --> 36:12.561
about the role that Mr. Ruzek
plays in her life,

36:12.605 --> 36:16.435
about the role
that he plays in your life.

36:16.478 --> 36:19.394
And can you guarantee
that after being shot

36:19.438 --> 36:23.224
at close range,
nearly bleeding out,

36:23.268 --> 36:26.096
flatlining in the hospital,

36:26.140 --> 36:31.276
that there'll be no lasting
physical complications?

36:31.319 --> 36:34.235
- That's my hope.

36:34.279 --> 36:37.630
- How about
mental complications?

36:37.673 --> 36:41.416
Is it your opinion that after
being that close to death,

36:41.460 --> 36:44.680
there are no residual effects?

36:44.724 --> 36:47.727
- I don't know.

36:47.770 --> 36:49.772
- The CPD has given you
ample opportunity

36:49.816 --> 36:51.600
to take desk work
after this incident.

36:51.644 --> 36:53.254
You overruled your own doctors.

36:53.298 --> 36:56.083
Insisted on going back
to Intelligence.

36:56.126 --> 36:58.738
When was the last time someone
fired a weapon at you?

37:00.566 --> 37:02.655
- About four hours ago.

37:04.657 --> 37:07.268
- [laughs]

37:07.312 --> 37:10.706
[somber music]

37:10.750 --> 37:14.144
♪

37:14.188 --> 37:17.278
- Makayla's favorite snack...

37:17.322 --> 37:20.890
is tortilla chips dipped
in whipped cream.

37:20.934 --> 37:22.936
It's--well, it's disgusting.

37:22.979 --> 37:25.417
But she'll trade me for it
for eating her veggies, so,

37:25.460 --> 37:27.288
you know, you do what you do.

37:27.332 --> 37:29.812
She collects these pieces
of sea glass.

37:29.856 --> 37:32.293
We go up to Loyola Beach
on Sunday mornings,

37:32.337 --> 37:34.077
if I'm not working.

37:34.121 --> 37:36.166
And she's obsessed with them.

37:36.210 --> 37:37.298
My pockets are full of them.

37:37.342 --> 37:38.343
Sometimes
I think they're multiplying.

37:38.386 --> 37:40.867
- Your Honor.

37:42.434 --> 37:44.653
- Makayla's discovered
that we have a freckle

37:44.697 --> 37:46.873
inside of the same toe
on the same foot.

37:46.916 --> 37:48.962
And she's decided
that we can communicate

37:49.005 --> 37:50.703
as a result, telepathically.

37:50.746 --> 37:53.053
So when she's at school,
like in the middle of the day,

37:53.096 --> 37:54.663
she sends me happy thoughts.

37:54.707 --> 37:56.709
And when I come home,
I'm supposed to know

37:56.752 --> 37:59.755
what those happy thoughts were,
which is hard.

37:59.799 --> 38:01.496
♪

38:01.540 --> 38:04.107
You were right
about pretty much everything.

38:04.151 --> 38:05.326
I don't have a ton of money.

38:05.370 --> 38:07.633
I don't have a ton of time,
a big house.

38:07.676 --> 38:11.114
Yes, Adam Ruzek, my ex-fiancé,
is moving in with us.

38:11.158 --> 38:14.117
I don't know how to explain
that except that we're family.

38:14.161 --> 38:17.120
And, yes, I almost died
and went back to a job

38:17.164 --> 38:20.341
when I didn't have to,
but it was what I needed then.

38:20.385 --> 38:23.779
And it's what I want now.

38:23.823 --> 38:25.433
I'm good at my job.

38:25.477 --> 38:28.349
I help people, and I'm proud
that my kid sees me doing that.

38:28.393 --> 38:30.656
I am a mess,
and I make mistakes.

38:30.699 --> 38:34.442
Makayla, that's something that
I've done pretty damn right.

38:34.486 --> 38:36.923
Theo, I--I get
what you're trying to do.

38:36.966 --> 38:40.361
Truly, truly, I do.

38:40.405 --> 38:41.797
But what Makayla and I have,

38:41.841 --> 38:44.278
you can't just snap
your fingers and make that up.

38:46.933 --> 38:49.065
It's real.

38:49.109 --> 38:51.851
She's my family.
And I'm hers.

38:51.894 --> 38:58.814
♪

39:07.432 --> 39:10.522
- We'll make the murders?
- Yeah, all three.

39:10.565 --> 39:12.175
There was tons of evidence
in the warehouse--

39:12.219 --> 39:14.003
more video, social media.

39:14.047 --> 39:15.396
- Any of it make sense
with the hands?

39:15.440 --> 39:17.224
- Yeah, part of Micah's message

39:17.267 --> 39:19.487
was that these men were trying
to strike at the family,

39:19.531 --> 39:20.923
tear them down.

39:20.967 --> 39:23.056
So the women had to take
their hands, their fists,

39:23.099 --> 39:24.884
as a preemptive strike.

39:24.927 --> 39:26.015
- And Jackie Williams?

39:26.059 --> 39:27.452
- Yeah, I got her a deal
with the ASA.

39:27.495 --> 39:29.236
She'll be back home
with her brother.

39:29.279 --> 39:30.803
- That's good work.

39:30.846 --> 39:32.108
Hmm.

39:32.152 --> 39:33.414
- Yeah.

39:33.458 --> 39:36.286
- For what it's worth...

39:36.330 --> 39:38.637
I'd bet on you every time.

39:44.904 --> 39:47.820
[phone vibrating]

39:54.174 --> 39:57.177
- This is Kim.

39:57.220 --> 39:59.701
Yeah, I can talk.

39:59.745 --> 40:03.139
[soft dramatic music]

40:03.183 --> 40:10.364
♪

40:14.760 --> 40:16.283
Adam!

40:16.326 --> 40:18.416
[laughs]

40:18.459 --> 40:19.634
We won!

40:19.678 --> 40:21.462
- Are you kidding me?

40:21.506 --> 40:22.811
- [laughs]

40:22.855 --> 40:24.030
- Tell me what the judge said.

40:24.073 --> 40:25.466
- I guess, bottom line is

40:25.510 --> 40:27.033
who the child's
most bonded with,

40:27.076 --> 40:30.123
so--so she's ours.

40:30.166 --> 40:31.951
- You are my hero right now.

40:31.994 --> 40:33.474
Oh, my God!

40:33.518 --> 40:34.867
- [laughs]
- Oh.

40:37.826 --> 40:38.914
All right, let's go see her.

40:38.958 --> 40:40.612
- Let's go see our kid.
- All right.

40:40.655 --> 40:42.222
- Champagne and pizza.

40:42.265 --> 40:44.398
It's very upstairs, downstairs.
- You'd think.

40:44.442 --> 40:45.660
It's actually
an expensive pizza

40:45.704 --> 40:47.314
and a very cheap bottle
of champagne.

40:47.357 --> 40:50.317
- [laughs]

40:50.360 --> 40:53.015
[intense music]

40:53.059 --> 40:55.496
Gabby?
- Jesus.

40:55.540 --> 40:57.193
Find Mack--find Makayla.

40:57.237 --> 40:58.543
Gabby, Gabby, it's Adam.

40:58.586 --> 40:59.848
Gabby, hey!

40:59.892 --> 41:03.025
Hey, what happened?
Where's Makayla?

41:03.069 --> 41:05.550
- Mak--
[gurgles]

41:05.593 --> 41:07.029
♪

41:07.073 --> 41:09.902
- Makayla?

41:09.945 --> 41:12.905
[panting]

41:12.948 --> 41:16.561
♪

41:20.260 --> 41:20.608
.

41:20.652 --> 41:23.393
[dramatic music]

41:23.437 --> 41:30.575
♪

41:49.942 --> 41:52.901
[wolf howls]
